brainly_data.question: What did the united states senate vote to do after world war i?
brainly_data.subject: History

all_answers.question: What did the united states senate vote to do after world war i?
all_answers.subject: History
all_answers.text: On this day in 1919, the Senate spurned the Treaty of Versailles that had endedWorld War I and provided for a new world body, championed by President Woodrow Wilson, called the League of Nations. ... Those twin votes marked the first time theSenate had ever rejected a peace treaty
